(RecordsStashed (2 737 [(kchq ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Principle [NOTA extension programming is structural matching over nodes. The parser first preserves raw delimiter structure, object counts, sigils, and nested block shapes; then ordered macro-node definitions match that structure using constraints, most-specific first, and absence of a match is a formatting or specification error.] Zero VeryHigh Zero [])) (ut6z ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [Every registration of a new referent is gated by the guardian, the same as records, not admitted by a self-service synonym check alone *validation*] Zero VeryHigh Zero [])) (zgi8 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [The Spirit guardian is the single locus of judgment and the model checks everything semantic — consistency, duplication, trample, non-intent — with only structural admission staying upstream as input validation] Zero VeryHigh Zero [])) (2t89 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Principle [A well-specialized, clean-context, well-instructed guardian can outperform the submitting agent at judging a capture even on a nominally weaker model, because the agent is buried in noise from messy interaction and code while the guardian judges one case at full attention with extensive on-point instructions. The lever for a smarter guardian is specialization, clean context, and training, not raw model strength; a larger-context model like DeepSeek Pro helps only when paired with proper training. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (3ufq ([(Information Curation)] Decision [The goal of context maintenance is to reduce the number of reports without losing information, by agglomerating topics: multiple reports on a topic are rewritten and merged into one Refresh report per topic, preserving the un-contradicted and un-superseded substance in a better form. Refresh is the report variant tag — the Capital word after the number — for such a rewritten or agglomerated report; one Refresh report may merge several source reports, which are then deleted with the Refresh report as the landing witness.] Zero High Zero [])) (4jgt ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Constraint [The guardian must always return a well-formed NOTA response; a malformed guardian response must never happen. Its instructions must specify the exact response format unambiguously, with the verdict grammar and the closed rejection-reason set generated into the prompt, plus a parse-and-retry and a shape test, so an out-of-format reply is impossible in practice. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (5hjv ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Constraint [All Spirit Signal, Nexus, and SEMA operations must be declared in the schema files first; generated schema types are the source of every operation data type, and handwritten Rust may only implement behavior on those generated nouns.] Zero High Zero [])) (813q ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Decision [|The canonical pipeline: authored schema (NOTA) deserializes via the structural-macro-node codec directly into schema-in-rust (typed, rkyv-serializable, canonical round-trip), which then lowers into Rust interface code.|] Zero High Zero [])) (88mw ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [The guardian needs proper per-operation prompts: each operation type gets detailed guidance with worked examples of what passes as an accept and what is rejected and why. Over-train the guardian first with rich, detailed instructions and many examples, then scale back once it works, because the guardian calls are currently undertrained. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (8bwo ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Every component exposes its two contracts, the working signal and the meta policy signal, as two thin CLI clients: the working client named after the component and the meta client prefixed meta-. This is one extracted pattern applied across all components with minimal per-component hand-coding, not re-implemented per component. Spirit spirit and meta-spirit are the first instance.] Zero High Zero [])) (a71r ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [|Every component engine in the workspace triad architecture defines and uses its Signal, Nexus, and SEMA interfaces in schema, and conducts core logic through schema-emitted traits whose methods take and return root types of the concerned interfaces — adapting Spirit 1326 (spirit-engine-specific) to the workspace-wide component-triad pattern. The trait surface is uniform across components; each component's runtime is a composition of schema-emitted trait implementations.|] Zero High Zero [])) (ans1 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [The upgraded justification is a strongly-typed structured argued case: typed verbatim testimony with optional antecedents, plus a reasoning that argues why the record should be admitted and why its certainty, domain, kind, and importance are right. The claim is the operation own Entry, never a justification sub-field. It is never a stringly-typed blob. Redundant citation-signal tags are excluded; a cited record relationship is carried by the operation or by the reasoning prose. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (bwqe ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [Ship the lean core of the intent-justification upgrade first: typed verbatim testimony plus a check that the quoted words actually support the claimed certainty, with a binary guardian verdict. Defer the elaborate court structure, the typed warrant sub-sections, a separate stakes-basis slot, and cross-record motions-as-precedent, to a later phase, adding each only where the lean core demonstrably falls short. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (dqg3 ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Principle [Anything that needs to be done to test something is done IN the test. When a test is blocked by missing infrastructure, the test mocks, stubs, hand-codes, or builds the minimal version of the missing piece to make the test run. Coming back with we cant test this because of a blocker is the wrong response - unblock the blocker IN THE TEST, exercise the design end-to-end, see what actually works, what does not, and how it works. Tests are where you get to do whatever you need to do; thats their point.] Zero High Zero [])) (gad7 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [Supersede must support replacing a retired set with multiple new intents in one atomic operation, not just a single replacement. The reason is correctness, not convenience: when the content of the retired records splits into several new records, replacing them with a single record loses meaning and the guardian should refuse it, so superseding with several replacements must be one operation the guardian judges as a whole, asking whether the new set together preserves the kernel of the retired set. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (hnpo ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [MetaSignal is the canonical name for the policy and authority contract; OwnerSignal is deprecated. Every component policy contract is named meta-signal then component uniformly, including ones whose repos are absent or still owner-signal-prefixed today — meta-signal-persona, meta-signal-criome, and meta-signal-agent are born meta-signal, never owner-signal. This confirms and generalizes record r9qy from its specific repo rename list to the universal naming principle, and answers system-designer report 77 decision 1: from-scratch policy contracts are born meta-signal.] Zero High Zero [])) (iplo ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [The cloud-designer prototype method is a development cycle: mine existing intent + reports + code for working solutions, implement a fully-working prototype that uses all designed components, then audit the prototype against the full designed surface. Audit gaps drive iterative growth of the underlying components themselves — each prototype iteration grows BOTH prototype completeness AND the component capabilities the prototype needs to use fully. Component development is co-developed through prototype use, not as separate work.] Zero High Zero [])) (jh0r ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [No stringly-typed types anywhere — the psyche calls them bullshit types. Prefer value enums that break a field into its closed set of possibilities; enums are clear and self-descriptive and still carry the data each variant owns. Reach for an enum over a bare string or bool whenever a field has enumerable cases.] Zero High Zero [])) (ll41 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [An intent submission carries a justification that argues the case for the intent: the submitting agent sells why this should become intent, embedding the psyche verbatim words with the surrounding context of what was discussed and proposed. A justification can quote several verbatim fragments and can reference previously recorded intents. Verbatim spans in a justification are surrounded by asterisks. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (lpk9 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling))) (Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Correction [Schema struct bodies must not accept the old field Type pair syntax. Struct bodies are positional lists of field types; an explicit field name different from the type uses the dot differentiator such as source.TypeReference. The schema reader should reject the old pair form rather than silently accepting it.] Zero High Zero [])) (n5p2 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [The schema creates the data types and those generated types must be used in the logic flow, not ignored or bypassed. Logic threads the schema-emitted types end to end rather than re-deriving or re-encoding their content by hand.] Zero High Zero [])) (niv3 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [Spirit category is a closed enum with a broad category-theory starting set, not a narrow free-text topic field.] Zero High Zero [])) (nqsb ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Every repository must have an INTENT.md, and it is the FIRST file to create for a repo — the most important file, answering: what is this repository for? A repo's INTENT.md holds the most important AND ONLY the most important design intent and design constraints that concern that project; it is curated and distilled to the essential, not an accumulation of everything. Isolating the most important design constraints into each repo's INTENT.md is a priority, and Psyche reports explaining a repo should be based on its reviewed/curated INTENT.md. Per psyche 2026-06-04.] Zero High Zero [])) (oyli ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [The intent unit is named domain, a specific grounded subject grouped under broad areas; the terms category and topic are retired] Zero High Zero [])) (pguv ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [|Valid lane shapes are <role>, second-<role>, third-<role>, and qualified-prefix-<role> (e.g. system-<role>, cluster-<role>, pi-<role>).|] Zero High Zero [])) (pr61 ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Principle [Domain tree depth is proportional to intent density, not a structural exception: Software nests deeper because it holds far more, while sparse Hardware stays one level.] Zero High Zero [])) (q0ag ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Correction [DomainScope operations must stay typed all the way through matching, expansion, and equivalence; converting recursive enum values into Debug strings or Vec String paths is not an acceptable implementation.] Zero High Zero [])) (qpv6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl))) (Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Decision [For the current SEMA version-control implementation, keep the work in sema-engine now rather than creating a new sema-vcs repository. A later extraction remains possible after the engine nouns settle.] Zero High Zero [])) (si3j ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Decision [The existing agent component is draft evidence with low authority; if it conflicts with the current Spirit intent redesign and broker-daemon harness architecture, operator should disregard, replace, or delete the old shape rather than preserve compatibility. *maintenance*] Zero High Zero [])) (so3b ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Principle [Certainty is the burden of proof the verbatim testimony must clear. The submitting agent proposes a burden by claiming a certainty level, and the psyche verbatim quotes must clear that level on their modal strength. An over-claimed certainty on hedged words fails its burden and is rejected; the guardian never silently lowers the level. This makes honest understatement the rational strategy because a lower claim faces an easier bar. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (t7h0 ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Constraint [Full correctness means every pipeline step is genuinely implemented end-to-end and does its real job; green tests are not correctness. Design-implementation avoidance — the common bootstrapping failure mode — is forbidden.] Zero High Zero [])) (t803 ([(Technology (Software (Security Authorization)))] Clarification [The basic baseline meta operations of every meta-signal-component contract are daemon configuration: the meta plane carries a Configure operation that applies the component typed daemon configuration. This is the foundational content of the meta contract; component-specific privileged runtime actions build on top. Consistent with binary-only startup, where the daemon startup record is itself a binary meta-signal configuration message and later configuration arrives as authenticated meta-signal Configure messages, never flags.] Zero High Zero [])) (tgch ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [The Spirit triad engine should be interface-first: schema-defined root interfaces generate the Signal, Nexus, and SEMA message types and actor traits; handwritten runtime code should stay terse, matching decisions, invoking algorithms, routing replies, and never bypassing the schema-defined trait boundaries. Signal owns communication triage and final replies, Nexus owns central decision-making across the outer Signal side and inner SEMA side, and SEMA owns durable state management. The intended flow is Signal input to Nexus input, Nexus to SEMA input when state work is needed, SEMA output back to Nexus, Nexus output back to Signal, and Signal output back to the client.] Zero High Zero [])) (u62s ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Certainty and importance are orthogonal axes and must never be conflated. A tentative idea can carry very low certainty yet high importance: it is not decided but it matters. Capture sets the two independently and neither substitutes for the other.] Zero High Zero [])) (vbx6 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Spirit records should distinguish certainty from weight: certainty is confidence in the statement, while weight is accumulated importance or reinforcement, especially for composite records derived from multiple source records.] Zero High Zero [])) (woku ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [Intent capture must preserve the psyche modality and never upgrade tentative wording into confident assertion: when the psyche hedges with I think, I feel like, could, or maybe, the recorded certainty must stay low and the wording must not be rewritten from could into should or from a feeling into a fact. The guardian needs visibility into how the psyche actually worded the statement and rejects over-stated capture. The guardian stays a binary yes-or-no gate and never silently lowers certainty itself, because a rejection sends the thinking back to the submitting agent, the highest-thinking-power model, who reconsiders and rewords; keeping the gate binary keeps the thinking where it belongs. *admission control*] Zero High Zero [])) (xo9g ([(Knowledge Taxonomy)] Decision [Cross-tree domain relations are symmetric equivalence only — synonyms that retrieve together both ways. Directional subsumption between domains is dropped because the nested tree and scope-prefix matching already carry all hierarchy.] Zero High Zero [])) (xx2l ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|Schema files live with their contract's source-of-truth, and a repo may hold multiple .schema files (one per contract) named <crate>/<contract-name>.schema, superseding the prior one-schema-per-repo assumption.|] Zero High Zero [])) (yfw5 ([(Technology (Software (Security SecretsManagement)))] Constraint [The local LLM API token is installed into local agent configuration through the standard managed Home-profile path as a command-backed gopass reference - for Pi an auth.json entry whose value runs gopass at call time - never a literal key written into Nix source or models.json. Applies the never-expose-plaintext rule of records 1011 1012 to the local-agent auth path; the prometheus llama-server now enforces the token so the prior dummy sk-no-key-required no longer authenticates.] Zero High Zero [])) (yhn9 ([(Information Archives)] Decision [Introduce an archive system as a specialized sema-database that holds exactly one kind of archived object, with the database name stating what it archives. Pair it with a small archive-retrieving tool that reads archived objects back. Designer concepts the shape, operator implements. This is the durable home for collected removal candidates and other archived component data; the concept validates the exact shape.] Zero High Zero [])) (0fs6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [owner-signal-persona is the deprecated OwnerSignal form and should become meta-signal-persona, and signal-engine-management is an off-pattern name that should fold into the signal-persona / meta-signal-persona pair.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (1gho ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Principle [Short headers should encode enough top-level variant shape for cheap routing.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (4ups ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [The -next replacement repos have won and their originals are deprecated: nota-next is the canonical NOTA implementation and schema-next with schema-rust-next the canonical schema-derived stack, superseding the old nota and schema repos which the psyche no longer cares for. The -next suffix is now vestigial ancestry and should be dropped, renaming the replacements to their base names.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (51sf ([(Technology (Software (Systems SystemsProgramming)))] Clarification [Ownership split refining bcca: orchestrate owns cell instance lifecycle policy and ordering, systemd owns the OS process supervision and restart-survival, and terminal-control owns the durable sema instance record used to reattach.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (569t ([(Technology (Software (Security Authorization)))] Constraint [A content daemon must have no ambient access to system private-key material and, handed a path to a private key, must be unable to read it. *access control*] Zero Medium Zero [])) (5pfy ([(Technology (Software (Programming Metaprogramming)))] Decision [|The Rust emitter must consume the serialized assembled form (checked-in or build-time-emitted .asschema NOTA files), not the in-memory Rust value directly.|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (5xss ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [The structural-match pattern language is a typed enum of primitives — arity, atom-case, atom-sigil, delimiter-type, atom literal — bounded so the macro data stays serializable.] Zero 