e abstracted behind the agent component.|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (ai4j ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [|The macro generates a Tier-1 64-bit small-header per enum (LogVariant + frame_micro projection).|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (bw7s ([(Language Correspondence)] Principle [Visuals belong in reports, not chat, and may be used freely there when needed.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (c2dc ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [|The NOTA decoder is extended by a registry of registered macros dispatched as an ordered list (first match wins) with conflict detection at registry-construction time; the captured blocks are interpreted by a consumer (Schema being one consumer).|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (dv9a ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [Each plane has its own engine and traits but all three share the pattern of running code over an input message and returning an output message with populated data.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (e2px ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Modularity)))] Clarification [Why a component contract is split into separate signal-component and meta-signal-component repositories rather than living in the daemon repo. First, rebuild-churn isolation: peers that only need to talk to a component depend on the small contract repo, so they recompile only when the wire contract changes, not when the component internal logic, runtime, or documentation changes; keeping the contract in the daemon repo would rebuild every dependent on any internal edit. Second, security-sensitivity visibility: owner-only operations live in a distinct meta-signal repo, making security-sensitive edits obvious and letting clients that do not need owner authority avoid depending on it. Third, meta-signal is optional: some components have no owner relationship and only need the ordinary signal contract to talk to peers. The split is about compilation and dependency isolation and authority clarity, not about where state or logic lives.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (e9gr ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Gap-fill from forwarded operator prompt: owner-signal surfaces should become core-signal surfaces; core owns the privileged control and library layer, while signal-* remains the ordinary messaging layer for safer callers and extensions.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (f6i5 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|PRETTY horizon computes the pre-derived helper variables Nix consumes (behaves-as/gating booleans, resolved magnitudes, lid-switch policy, trust-gated extra-groups) in typed Rust, NOT in Nix composition; Nix only uses the already-derived variables.|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (fc3j ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Decision [Asynchronous representation lives at the data-type level of the Signal Protocol: the message data types themselves carry the correlation IDs and lifecycle state tracking sent/queued/processing/replied transitions.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (fvf1 ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Decision [Tests must prove, not pretend: audit existing tests for genuineness, treat in-process synthetic-state tests as lesser proof than real-binary-via-Nix tests, and replace identified pretend-tests with full-stack Nix integration tests. *integration testing*] Zero Medium Zero [])) (g9no ([(Technology (Software (Programming Metaprogramming)))] Decision [The schema authoring language is itself a macro that expands to assembled-schema data, and once bootstrapped the schema-of-schemas generates its own assembled and short-syntax forms, closing the self-hosting loop.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (hnoo ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Decision [|Audits feed into bead filing focused on (a) bringing code into constraint (constraint tests, falsifiable specs per skills/architectural-truth-tests.md, type-system witnesses) and (b) end-to-end sandboxed engine testing (Nix-flake-based integration tests exercising full daemon-to-daemon paths). Audits are the natural input to constraint-tightening + integration-coverage filing|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (i13x ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|A component's runtime LOGIC structure is a triad of Signal (reactive external surface), an internal-decision layer, and SEMA (single-writer state layer interfacing storage); this runtime triad lives inside the <component> daemon repo.|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (i9qv ([(Technology (Software (Security Authentication)))] Principle [Possessing cryptographic identity is what lets an agent express opinions through signatures — existing in the Criome is having the power to sign.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (ix9y ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Clarification [|What survives from the original interaction records: the two-languages distinction (internal effect vs external wire), effect-table match-driven dispatch as schema closing message-to-method mapping, and actor fan-out execution as what methods return. *design pattern*|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (j487 ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Constraint [The version-controlled server-backed atomic durability mechanism for component Sema databases must be built once as a reusable library of generic types and traits, not reimplemented per component. Every component is to have the option to version-control its state through this one shared mechanism. The reusable-library direction is firm; the exact generic mechanism is undesigned and to be settled by prior-art research and implementation experiments. Extends 29pb.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (jtmt ([(Technology (Software (Security Authentication)))] Decision [|The public key IS the agent identifier — there is no separate UID storage; a single storage primitive (the key) carries every identifier length.|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (k9kl ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Decision [|Canonical integration-test shape: real .schema files in real project paths drive Nix code generation; the spirit CLI and daemon are built by Nix; tests launch the binaries, the CLI sends real rkyv signal frames over a real Unix socket, the Nexus executor (with its own typed input/output) processes and returns, SEMA holds durable state, and the reply comes back through the whole chain end-to-end — every component driven off the schema. *integration testing*|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (kgl2 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Principle [Message-sent is an event surface with behavior: the mail dispatch system should emit or commit a typed MessageSent action that hooks, UI layers, routers, or subscribers can react to immediately.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (l01b ([(Technology (Hardware Networking))] Constraint [Prometheus router USB backup network devices must be optional: their absence must not make router networking fail, and USB Ethernet or Wi-Fi devices plugged in after boot should be configured when they appear.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (l489 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [The macro emits NOTA encoding/decoding capability from the same schema source.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (lekz ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Correction [The InteractTrait abstraction and the interaction-actor concept are retracted as overengineered: a method call on an actor IS the interaction; schema-rust composer must not emit Interact<Input> or InteractionActor<Input> traits. *design pattern*] Zero Medium Zero [])) (lhr4 ([(Technology (Software (Systems Concurrency)))] Decision [Schema may declare semantic constraints such as ordering, idempotence, cancellability, read fanout, or single-writer requirements only when those semantics are real.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (lo72 ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [The -specialist lane suffix is retired; system-specialist becomes system-operator, and similar specialist lanes rename to their base role.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (ltfr ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [The dispatcher assigns the subagent a report number inside the dispatcher's own role report subdirectory; subagent dispatches write into the dispatcher's role subdir, never into a separate assistant-named subdir.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (m2ri ([(Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Decision [Rename persona-llm-client to `agent`, dropping the persona- prefix.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (nfic ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Clarification [For Crayon OS host maintenance, the maintainer has root SSH access on all cluster hosts but cannot SSH as Bird on Zeus; Bird's Zeus home-profile redeploy must use an existing root or maintainer-user path rather than direct Bird SSH.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (nj2n ([(Technology (Software (Programming Parsing)))] Decision [|NOTA parsing breaks down by object using positional ranges. Each block tracks its source span (line/column for both start and end on the original text). Each block carries methods/predicates to query its structure: is_square_bracket_block / is_parenthesis_block / is_brace_block; holds_single_root_object / holds_two_root_objects / holds_N_root_objects; recursive predicates like second_root_object_is_a_square_bracket_object / second_root_object_qualifies_as_a_symbol. Recursion: each root object inside a block is itself a typed/positioned block. The recursive parsing chain IS the chain of block-level queries.|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (nq28 ([(Technology (Software (Observability Tracing)))] Decision [Trace names are macro-emitted from the schema-defined enum variant structure rather than free-floating strings; the macro generated the variant so it already owns the activated object's identifier.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (nszl ([(Technology (Software (Programming Parsing)))] Decision [Schema parsing operates in multiple passes per source block. Pass 1 finds all identifier uses and their source locations. Pass 2 registers inline declarations into the namespace and resolves identifier references through namespace lookup. This supports the shorthand syntax where a header variant can be bare PascalCase looked up in namespace inline declaration auto-registered or explicit Variant Payload form. The multi-pass approach lets the engine know whether each identifier defines a type references a type or both — guesswork is eliminated by the source representation rather than rediscovered from lowered fields.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (oog6 ([(Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Decision [Agent is a supervised component used by other components that want pre-configured API agent calls, not a thin wrapper.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (p1dt ([(Technology (Software (Systems SystemsProgramming)))] Decision [|terminal-cell processes are forked via systemd so a cell survives a terminal-control restart — the cell is a systemd-managed process, not a child of terminal-control; on restart terminal-control rediscovers still-running cells from sema and reattaches to their control and data sockets, realizing the abduco survive-detach property through systemd (OS supervision) plus sema (durable instance registry).|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (p31j ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [The macro emits a VersionProjection between the current and next schema versions as the next-version-as-dependency upgrade path.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (p6j5 ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Decision [Cloud's Plan operation is renamed to Mutate, and its acknowledged-state reply is renamed Mutated. *replication*] Zero Medium Zero [])) (qem1 ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Constraint [Each mandatory pipeline step must be proven by real file-based tests: NOTA structural parse, the single shared codec in nota-next, schema read against the schema-of-schemas, macro/declaration assembly into macro-free Asschema data, the roots model, Rust emission of datatypes and derive-based trait impls over the shared codec, and the hand-written actor system running full constraints on spirit-