pe: a root-layer struct with macro-expanded fields all the way down to scalar leaves; the top-level schema document IS a known struct named at the dialect level (the basic schema definition / Schema) with positional fields of known types; if a field is a vector it carries a variable number of macro-call instances; macros ARE structural expansion based on position; inner struct or enum declarations are themselves macros that fire at their positions; the objects inside a macro call become the MATCH against the macro pattern; enum bodies get re-parsed because the enum name carries forward; the recursion terminates at FINAL built-in macros expanding leaf structs or enums whose fields are only SCALAR types: vectors of integers, vectors of unit-variant enums, booleans, integers, strings; strings at the language level are typed newtypes around character sequences for proper identity not bare strings; this gives a uniform structural model from the root schema document down to every scalar position - position determines type, macros do structural expansion, leaves are scalars|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (xyqt ([(Information Documentation)] Decision [|A Spirit record is cited as the bracket-quoted description plus a (Spirit Kind short) parenthetical.|] Zero Medium Zero [])) (y1qw ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Correction [Single-field schema declarations without an explicit field name should lower and emit as newtypes, not named one-field structs. A PascalCase self-named field or single referenced type is a semantic type object; only multi-field structs derive lowercase field names. Generated Rust and NOTA should preserve this by using transparent newtypes so trace events like ObjectName do not become double-delimited one-field records.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (y4rl ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces Visualization)))] Constraint [Each design graph should be paired with the relevant code surface it depicts.] Zero Medium Zero [])) (y9c6 ([(Technology (Softwar