nformation Documentation)] Constraint [The full random record hash stays binary on the wire; only the short prefix appears in text.] Zero Low Zero [])) (lc7e ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [Existing designer-assistant reports should be renamed into the designer lane so operator and other roles can see them.] Zero Low Zero [])) (lw51 ([(Information Documentation)] Principle [Topic labels are drawn from a controlled topic vocabulary maintained per workspace through use.] Zero Low Zero [])) (my86 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [A file's entire structure is itself a typed tree of nodes — structural forms — each of which recognises a block by its shape and recursively decodes its children. There is no parser to hand-write: the grammar is the type, the type is the reader, and the recursive shape match stands in for parsing. This is the structural realization behind the aski goal — elegant syntax is not produced by parsing logic but falls out of declaring the typed nodes as data.] Zero Low Zero [nota-next schema-next aski])) (nfje ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [Bare signal-persona references in docs are correct and must NOT be migrated away.] Zero Low Zero [])) (nh0t ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|terminal-control is NOT folded into harness (AI-only, would orphan non-harness cells) nor into orchestrate (which owns coordination identity not delivery identity); orchestrate owns cell instance lifecycle policy as an order plane.|] Zero Low Zero [])) (pumu ([(Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Decision [The Pi harness ships with packaged Pi extensions.] Zero Low Zero [])) (tt8a ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [terminal-cell stays the abduco primitive and absorbs the input-gate writer and prompt-matcher currently duplicated with terminal.] Zero Low Zero [])) (z7a7 ([(Technology (Software Systems))] Clarification [terminal-cell is NOT a triad engine component and NOT a managed service daemon; its current non-triad shape is incidental — it predates the triad engine — not a deliberate end-state. *virtualization*] Zero Low Zero [])) (p3td ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture))) (Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [criome is a universal agreement machine for authorizations - the agreement-and-authorization organ of Telos, the meta-project, not Telos itself. The quorum is criome's universal primitive: everything is a quorum. Each principal runs more than one node and asks its own quorum to make its attestations reliable and its timestamps credible - forging an attestation would require compromising a threshold of the principal's own nodes rather than a single node, so a self-quorum across one's own nodes is a reliability mechanism, not only multi-party trust across different principals. One quorum primitive serves both, scoped by membership: a principal's own nodes for reliability and credible time, multiple principals for cross-party trust.] Zero VeryLow Zero [criome])) (00zx ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Decision [Per-type Migration trait includes a self-check / peer-coordination message that knows whether to consult the next-version daemon] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (0678 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Stable public signal schemas belong in contract repositories separate from daemon logic crates, so consumers compile against stable interface crates and are not rebuilt merely because a daemon's internal logic changes. Generated Rust for the contract may be checked in as a reference, while build-time consumers must avoid duplicating foreign trait implementations or creating unnecessary wrapper newtypes.] Zero Minimum Zero [signal-spirit spirit signal schema-rust-next schema-next])) (06jd ([(Work Productivity)] Decision [When an agent passes surfaces many open psyche questions, the move is to LEAN on pattern-reco