ment)))] Decision [The CriomOS VM-testing node gains a durable on-demand mode for continual production-side OS testing — a persistent VM node defined in cluster data and homed on prometheus that is not booted by default but started on demand, so the production OS can be tested in a real VM on the production host as an ongoing development-and-validation target. The host-untouched boundary for this durable node is scoped: prometheus MAY carry the typed VmHost KVM-hosting capability declared in its generation, since that is the infrastructure that lets it host the VMs, while prometheus networking, the router, and production function stay untouched. The not-booted-by-default mode keeps the guest and its routed networking inactive until a test is started, and any activation on the live router uses BootOnce rather than a live switch-to-configuration. This extends the VM-testing node feature y1v5, cncj placement of the routed test VM on prometheus, and se72 cutover validation from one-off transient runs toward a durable continually-available target, and reconciles with 7let by permitting the KVM-host infrastructure touch while keeping everything else untouched. Its node-service shape follows qkvx as a real typed horizon-rs NodeService variant authored in datom.nota and projected typed rather than a string-keyed hack, superseding the garbage VmTesting work tracked by bead primary-wvey.] Zero Minimum Zero [prometheus horizon-rs lojix])) (7816 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [Multi-version dispatch protocol: CLI sends to the next-version daemon; next-version daemon coordinates back with main; missing-next returns error logged-as-failed] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (78cn ([(Technology (Software (Programming Metaprogramming)))] Principle [Schema namespace supports recursive type references — entries in the namespace can reference other namespace entries, allowing recursive data type definitions. Logic can be defined in the namespace through these rec