odify — and Modify subdivides into ContainerEmbed, EnumWrap, Reorder, and KeyChange sub-cases] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8f8e ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Principle [|The workspace should be able to test UI and visual components end-to-end in a sandbox — launch real applications the component affects, run the component, and observe the actual visual effect (theme change, screen warmth, brightness) while watching for system freezes and errors — to verify a component actually works, not merely compiles. Sandboxes can run via systemd and spawn on a node such as Prometheus. chroma (theme/warmth/brightness) is the first target. *e2e*|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8g9n ([(Information RecordKeeping)] Principle [Hard deletion of intent records is inevitable on a long enough timeline because storage is finite, so the design must treat hard deletion as a deliberate decision to plan for rather than a state to forbid] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8l6x ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [Spirit accepted-record reply schema should avoid nested summary-shaped acknowledgements] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8pgh ([(Technology (Software Intelligence))] Decision [Local Pi and agent sessions should be able to use the prometheus-hosted local LLM models, including the new Gemma 4 multimodal models, as a selectable local provider. This is the consumption side of the Gemma deploy of records 1015 1022 1032 1033: the models are served on prometheus and local agents should call them. *model inference*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8qnc ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Constraint [Large model prefetches and fixed-output hash discovery for CriomOS large-AI model inventory should run on Prometheus over its wired LAN path, not on the local workstation Wi-Fi. *provisioning*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8qt4 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Principle [claims start from clean checkout] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8ryy ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [Assembled root syntax must not represent Input and Output as a struct containing another single-field struct. If the root shape is known, the assembled form should carry the root bodies directly in their known positions or use a real common enum object; it should not add meaningless one-field wrapper records just to make vector syntax type-check.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8uid ([(Technology (Software Systems))] Decision [Create a dedicated rescue terminal for emergency desktop recovery, separate from ordinary terminal windows so it can receive protected interactive-resource policy without also boosting heavy agent or build children. *resource management*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8vjd ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [Schema MVP work should lean from durable intent, not only from discovered implementation gaps. *requirements*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8vrd ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Decision [Quantized Gemma model variants should be installed through the CriomOS/NixOS large-AI model inventory and deploy path, not left as ad-hoc prefetched files in the target store. *provisioning*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (8won ([(Technology (Software Data))] Correction [Spirit clients do not provide capture time *validation*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (9375 ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Correction [Legacy persona-spirit daemon slots that remain in the side-by-side deployed set are needed and should be fixed to run, not removed or disabled as the primary fix.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (94ee ([(Technology (Software (Engineering ApplicationProgrammingInterfaces)))] Principle [Do not keep old design convenience APIs after the working interface exists. The stack should keep one active working API moving forward and remove legacy or convenience surfaces instead of maintaining parallel ways to express the same runtime path.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (9gb7 ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [operator and second operator are one identity] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (9ngl ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces Visualization)))] Principle [mermaid graphs must be SHORT AND FOCUSED - aim 4-8 nodes per diagram with a hard cap around 10; bigger graphs are unreadable because the eye loses topology past 5-8 nodes and edges crisscross past that; when substance needs more than 8 nodes split into multiple focused diagrams each answering ONE question - data flow, type lineage, control flow, failure modes - rather than one big system map; siblings as separate top-level diagrams beat subgraphs inside a master diagram when partitions are clean; the reader takes each diagram in at a glance and composes the mental model across diagrams via surrounding prose; the test is whether a reader can take in the topology in one glance without scrolling or scanning - if no, factor] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (9ptu ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [Assembled schema is an expanded schema that can be processed as ordinary data structures. The assembled form should be data-first and macro-free, not a hidden parser control path.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (9qm8 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [criome may run as more than one deployment instance rather than one global daemon: a system criome for services and higher-privilege system concerns, and a user or home criome running in the owner home user space that any local client can connect to. Each remains an ordinary component with its two contracts; the split is about deployment instances and privilege tiers, not extra contracts. For now the single owner - the psyche - holds the system root privilege through the home criome. The Mentci approval daemon also running its own criome is an instance of the same per-principal-criome pattern. Exploratory and for-development - the psyche is not sure yet.] Zero Minimum Zero [criome])) (9rjq ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [Shipped runtime component binaries stay small and carry only their strict rkyv wire and storage contracts. The schema and NOTA compiler — nota-next, schema-next, schema-rust-next — is a build-time-only dependency that emits the typed Rust and never links into the runtime binary; the NOTA text codec is an optional edge feature absent from the daemon binary.] Zero Minimum Zero [rkyv schema-rust-next nota-next])) (9ryu ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Constraint [The signal-to-sema engine for the Spirit full-schema branch must have query and effect-to-response language schemas for each turn, with those schemas participating in the same schema-to-assembled-tree-to-Rust generation path.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (9s52 ([(Technology (Software (Security Authorization))) (Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Constraint [criome is per-Unix-user: each user runs their own home criome daemon with their own key custody, and the operating-system Unix-user boundary is the trust boundary. There is no single shared system criome that multiple users connect to with in-process separated lanes - that would collapse every user behind one daemon and one compromise point, a security risk. The privileged system criome tier from 9qm8 is for host-scoped system services under a service user, not a multi-user shared daemon; a user home criome peers with it for host-level facts rather than users sharing one criome. This is the same single-Unix-user custody boundary that rules out an embeddable criome engine library.] Zero Minimum Zero [criome])) (9ve7 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|Universal Interact trait: every object implements interact(other_object) that defines how two objects interact. The interaction uses the engines state implicitly (queried as needed including authorization checks); becomes async when waiting on outbound queries like Criome authorization; the actor system handles the wait so other code runs concurrently. The trait formalizes the workspace pattern that all logic is interactions between domains. *abstraction*|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (a7a7 ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [Handwritten Spirit runtime and test code should avoid nested generated alias wrapper construction such as Output rejected wrapping Rejected wrapping SignalRejection. Once alias lowering and generated constructors land upstream, handwritten code should use generated APIs such as Output rejected and Input record, or direct enum variants carrying the underlying payload for aliases.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (a7pe ([(Technology (Software (Operations ReleaseEngineering)))] Principle [Component code or logic changes should bump the component version, at least at patch level, so deployed binaries and reports do not keep stale version numbers after behavioral changes.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ad53 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Cloud-node OS images live in CriomOS as a minimal CloudNode-species profile, declaratively built with an image builder rather than by snapshotting a converted running droplet, and content-sized so a node boots fast on the smallest sensible droplet — a multi-tens-of-GB image is unacceptable. The cloud daemon references the image by id through the existing HostPlan image_name field and never holds the image definition. CriomOS owns the image definition and provider-format build, and cloud owns snapshot-id selection and provisioning.] Zero Minimum Zero [cloud CriomOS Horizon])) (adnn ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Schema struct declarations are positional lists of types, mirroring how the data reads in NOTA, not name-value pairs. The field name is derived from the type by default, the bare type, retiring the star shorthand. A field needing an explicit name uses a dot-prefix differentiator, name-first, as in key.TypeReference. The name-value struct form is retired.] Zero Minimum Zero [schema nota])) (afa8 ([(T