at mixed vector.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (baav ([(Information Documentation)] Decision [|Reports use standard YAML front matter for metadata, not the semicolon-bracket pseudo-NOTA shape (; role [topics] [description] date role) that recent reports have been emitting. Rationale — YAML front matter plugs into standard markdown UI tooling (previewers, GitHub rendering, Obsidian, editor frontmatter parsers); valid markdown so renderers display reports cleanly; is the conventional metadata-on-markdown standard. The psyche has mentioned this preference before. skills/reporting.md should specify YAML front matter as the canonical report header form.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (bb83 ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Clarification [Cross-daemon cutover can be atomic by protocol *fault tolerance*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (bds6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [Keep the active repository set lean. Superseded, dead, duplicate, and stub repositories are archived rather than left to clutter the workspace; a smaller active set is better. 150 active repos is too many. *maintenance*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (bodd ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Clarification [The Signal contract repository question is workspace-wide, not cloud-local: every contract repo must be audited for whether it incorrectly carries internal Nexus or SEMA engine surfaces instead of only the messaging vocabulary that crosses the component boundary.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (bp8k ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Decision [For the cloud component, ignore the earlier prototype as the implementation authority and write the system fresh from the current desired shape.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (bpg9 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [A .asschema file is read against the known Asschema root struct, so the canonical text form should not need an outer parenthesized record wrapper. The reader can consume the root fields positional