 Principle [Authored workspace data files should prefer typed NOTA data: predictable file names and directories define the expected root type, usually a struct or sometimes a top-level enum selection or vector of records.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ct2i ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [.asschema files must be real NOTA serialized assembled-schema data. Human-readable debug witnesses are not .asschema and must be named as witnesses instead. Calling a non-NOTA witness .asschema is a wrong artifact boundary.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (cw5t ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Spirit should support composite intent records that reference older intent records as source material, so repeated or closely related intent can be agglomerated into a newer stronger record without losing provenance.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (d1bi ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [NOTA positional structs do not omit fields: a field is present in the record shape and carries a value, including explicit None when the schema has an optional value. For Spirit privacy ergonomics, the desired shape is targeted public/private shorthand operations that lower to the full verbose record shape, not omitted positional fields.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (d1wr ([(Technology (Hardware Networking))] Correction [The Prometheus backup Wi-Fi SSID should be criome-backup, not CRIOM Backup.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (d6he ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [The first end-to-end production milestone is the spirit -> vcs -> criome -> router -> mirror chain. When Spirit accepts a new log object, Spirit asks the local criome daemon to authenticate the exact content-addressed object/event for propagation. Criome trusts that local request because the system-side boundary will structurally ensure it came from Spirit, then verifies the request has the expected type/shape for a Spirit-authenticated object, signs or authorizes it under a cluster-root-admitted identity, and propagates the authenticated event through Router. Router is the transport fabric for the propagation; remote criome/mirror participants receive the authenticated event and the remote mirror fetches/restores the announced object state. This keeps criome auth-only, Router transport-only, and mirror as the object version-control substrate. Threshold/majority timing for when criome announces acceptance remains future criome contract logic, not a Router requirement for the first PoC slice.] Zero Minimum Zero [spirit criome router mirror])) (da5i ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [|Every component daemon binds and serves a meta socket - its meta-signal-<component> surface - at runtime, even when its only operation is Configure. The meta socket is the universal per-component policy and configuration channel, required for every component rather than only those with rich meta operations; it manifests the two-contracts structure (7sx6) and the Configure bootstrap-and-runtime model (ur16) as a live bound socket on each daemon.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (daht ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Principle [Signal is the first gate: invalid or unacceptable messages are rejected at the Signal layer and return to the client without reaching Nexus or SEMA. *message queuing*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ddtj ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Constraint [Schema files are NOTA documents: every .schema fixture used in tests must be NOTA-legal and parsable by nota-next before schema-specific lowering. Tests should exercise .schema files as real parseable NOTA artifacts, not non-NOTA sketches.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (de8i ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [|The lowering of schema-in-rust into Rust should be implemented as methods/a trait ON the schema objects themselves — each Rust-model noun (RustStruct, RustEnum, RustField, RustEnumVariant, and a TypeExpression type) renders itself, composing recursively and returning typed RustCode — NOT delegated to an external emitter/writer god-struct. The current lower_to_rust trait is a FACADE: its impls hand self to a RustEmitter/RustWriter that holds all the emit verbs (52-method RustWriter), so the verbs live on the god-struct while the model types are passive data. This is the methods-on-nouns discipline (records 712/882, verb-belongs-to-noun) applied to the emission step — symmetric with the deserialize arrow, which is already methods-on-the-types via the structural macro node codec. The cross-object logic (plane split, plane-type, projections) becomes its own type (a PlaneType) that the per-noun render methods consult, not a reason for a god-struct. Per psyche 2026-06-05.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (dfqp ([(Information Documentation)] Correction [When the psyche asks where a substantive explanation lives, the operator must either provide the exact report locator or state plainly that the explanation was incorrectly given in chat and backfill it into a report. Do not hedge with guessing language when the agent just authored the content.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (dhxm ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Correction [Reusable shell support should provide documented Nix store path redaction helpers, so agents do not repeatedly hand-write ad-hoc sed redactors in every command.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (dn3c ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Constraint [|Public-traffic routing during component-version cutover must be lossless (no missed messages, no dropped connections) AND client-transparent (one stable socket; clients do not perform discovery). Rules out CLI-discovery designs that require the client to ask Persona where the active daemon lives|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (dnvs ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [Spirit removal-candidate certainty should use a shared neutral Magnitude bottom rung named Zero, not Option None; Zero avoids Option confusion while remaining policy-neutral across components.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (dtwe ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Decision [Schema-generated Rust should emit into a dedicated schema module tree inside the crate source, with generated lib-style module files mirroring the schema module layout before the normal Rust build consumes them.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (dxmu ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Correction [|A reactive-schema surface written as ((Parse Expression) (Render Expression) (Evaluate Expression)) is not a clear enum surface under the current macro grammar: the first symbols Parse Render Evaluate sit as heads of parenthesized nodes and therefore read as macro/operator heads unless a distinct enum-variant context or explicit enum form is established. Do not use this as the canonical reactive input/output example without resolving the enum-variant versus macro-head distinction.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (e0gd ([(Technology (Software (Programming Parsing)))] Principle [Block reassembly after parsing: blocks concatenate one-after-another. The parser output is composable - blocks join sequentially. Reassembly does not require nesting reconstruction; parsed blocks are first-class units that can be re-emitted in order.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (e2si ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Correction [|Schema root input and output definitions should support inline payload definitions directly in the root vector, for example [Record { Topic * Description * }], rather than forcing operation roots to be separated from payload bodies through namespace retags when the inline form is the beautiful compact shape.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (e440 ([(Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Decision [SEMA engine implements durable state as a single-writer actor: queries, writes, mutations, additions. Database upgrade operations flow through SEMA per Spirit 1308. Reads run in parallel — redb supports concurrent MVC