e of objects (e.g. messaging/operations); second sub-vector is another standard part of a schema definition (e.g. type namespace for new object names). Designer 326 section 2 example was wrong because it was a single flat vector — that misses the section structure.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (edpz ([(Information Curation)] Decision [Report-triage protocol: backed-by-intent goes to architecture; unbacked surfaces as question; clear+backed+implementable becomes a bead] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (eeeo ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture))) (Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [signal-standard is a new shared schema holding only genuine cross-component standards - the vocabulary every component conforms to, not a grab-bag of conveniences. Its first and central content is the cross-component classification: the ComponentKind roster and the differentiator. It is the second non-component shared signal- library alongside signal-frame, imported by all component contracts with each component's local ComponentKind copy retired. Not signal-system, which is the system component's own contract and would be overloaded, and not signal-frame, whose charter is domain-free frame mechanics. The roster is closed-but-partitioned - a system or core zone plus reserved room to grow, modeled on the signal namespace partition - so adding a component is a local edit, not a workspace-wide rebuild. In the migration, signal-persona's ComponentPrincipal collapses into the imported ComponentKind with no persona-local alias.] Zero Minimum Zero [criome router])) (ejec ([(Technology (Software (Operations BuildSystem)))] Principle [avoid invoking nix store hash paths directly; use nix run, nix shell, or nix build --out-link with temporary symlinks] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ejum ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Clarification [Schema headers are ordered enum-root declarations, not namespace vectors.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (epn9 ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Clarification [The desired direction is to understand and pursue moving more runtime behavior logic into the schema/macro-generated interface itself: macros define the interface and can also generate default trait wrappers, hooks, and eventually behavior targets so hand-written runtime code only fills the domain-specific decisions and algorithms.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ernc ([(Technology (Software (Programming Metaprogramming)))] Principle [Schema imports can be namespace imports with optional selection] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ew3f ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Schema work gets its own repository named schema] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ewo6 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [NOTA should have a data-type declaration layer for composite type objects such as Vec and Optional and related Rust-like composite type constructors. Schema reads those NOTA-layer datatype objects instead of inventing vector and optional as schema-only sugar.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ezat ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Clarification [|In the spirit-next 408 prototype the signal-nexus-sema order is type-enforced by two mechanisms together: (1) the push method threads the next engine(s) as generic parameters, so SignalEngine::push_to_nexus names both NexusEngine and SemaEngine and NexusEngine::receive_pushed_signal names SemaEngine; (2) an AcceptedMail token whose ONLY constructor lives inside the SignalActor validation gate is the sole argument the nexus method accepts. Together these make SEMA unreachable except through Nexus and Nexus unreachable except through Signal, with no procedural bypass. The reverse path is the return value threading back, not a second set of pushes. The old procedural handle orchestration, SignalAccepted/FromMail/process_with, and the vestigial emitted NexusEngine::execute passthrough were deleted so the three trait-ordered engines are the SOLE live path (record 1030). *remote procedure call*|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (f0wm ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Spirit intent records should be shaped as specific variants whose fields match their semantic needs; private record variants carry privacy data, while public record variants should not carry unused privacy fields.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (f743 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [Nota does not own type declarations; schema owns declarations. Plain Nota or type-reference positions can name scalars or composites such as String and Vec without declaring a new type; type declarations use the positional struct, enum, and newtype forms.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (f7ju ([(Information Documentation)] Principle [Agents clarify psyche wording into the Spirit description] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (fc7l ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Constraint [Do not keep the Asschema compatibility projection or old Asschema-facing APIs around after the schema-in-Rust source path supersedes them; remove the compatibility surface rather than preserving old API shape. *maintenance*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (fhaj ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Decision [In schema-rust-next, bare namespace bindings such as Rejected SignalRejection should lower to schema_next::TypeDeclaration::Alias once upstream exposes it, emitting pub type Rejected = SignalRejection; rather than tuple newtypes. Genuine single-field struct-body declarations remain newtypes with new, payload, into_payload, and From<Payload>; enum associated constructors should not wrap aliases as newtypes; keyword-safe constructors such as continue lowering to r#continue stay preserved.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (fhyb ([(Technology (Software (Programming Parsing)))] Clarification [Schema parsing should first identify the NOTA object delimiters and their schema-language roles: parentheses for enum or variant objects, square brackets for vector-like object sequences and string-derived token vectors where legal, and curly brackets for name-value namespace maps.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (frdf ([(Technology (Software Programming))] Clarification [Square-bracket string delimiters are a brainstorm candidate, not a settled NOTA decision: the conceptual argument is that a string is a compact vector of characters, so bracketed string syntax could visually fit the vector model while avoiding quote conflicts.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (fv2a ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [Assembled schema is a typed Rust data model with a NOTA projection. Its Rust types include macro declarations, type declarations, and namespaces for reusable declarations; names must remain unique through module-qualified identity so assembled schema can refer to types from other modules, libraries, and crates. The future self-hosting path mirrors these Rust-defined asschema types back into schema shorthand, where schema checks and assembles its own types.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (fwor ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Decision [the workspace continuously rolls all components forward to the latest version of intent; agents update intent, architecture files, and beads everywhere rather than letting components fall behind on superseded intent; one component at a time is the test substrate, but documentation and beads track the universal current direction *maintenance*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (fyuz ([(Technology (Software (Operations BuildSystem)))] Constraint [Synthetic firmware gating work must stay generic and verified with constrained Nix checks.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (g055 ([(Technology (Software Data))] Principle [Cloud first state may be lossy provider-backed cache *caching*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (g3f2 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Decision [The schema-derived runtime is driven by THREE ENGINES - a signal engine, a nexus engine, and a sema engine - whose traits DEFINE THE ORDER of execution. The signal engine processes the incoming signal and pushes it to the nexus engine; the nexus engine has a trait method invoked when a signal is pushed to it, processes and gates it, and pushes onward to the sema engine; then the flow REVERSES - the sema reply returns through nexus and back out as the signal output. Push happens only on success: an invalid message is answered to the client directly with a rejection without proceeding; a valid signal pushes to nexus, and if nexus accepts it proceeds to sema. The push methods take the next engine as a parameter so the trait signatures themselves sequence signal then nexus then sema then back. Refines records 964 967 970 and 989 990 by naming three engines whose traits encode the ordering.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (gb87 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Clarification [Nexus is the execution engine, not executor. The executor concept and the signal-executor library role are superseded by the nexus execution plane; component request-execution belongs to nexus going forward.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (gc0n ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture))) (Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign))) (Technology (Software (Intelligence AgentSystems)))] Decision [criome contracts can be programmed to escalate a decision to a named adjudicator - a mechanical quorum, an LLM-assisted panel, a smarter agent, or the psyche, the human owner - whose signed content-addressed verdict criome only verifies. That verdict is a closed typed outcome over an already-submitted content-addressed object, not a carrier for newly-authored answer content. Criome only authorizes objects that come in for authorization. Program answers live inside the program's declared closed answer set. The Mentci/criome adjudication path is vote-on-existing-object: approve the suggested object, reject it, or defer/non-judge/escalate. If Mentci lets the psyche author a NOTA value - for example an LLM prompt, a replacement answer proposal, or another typed object - that is a separate editor and object-creation flow; the authored value must be admitted as its own content-addressed object before criome can authorize it. Two properties make the ladder humble and adaptive. First, non-judgment is a first-class adjudicator output: an adjudicator may decline to rule and escalate instead of forcing a verdict. Second, the default LLM adjudicator is trained to lean toward rendering non-judgment - abstaining and escalating to a smarter agent or agents and to a psyche or psyches - rather than deciding a case it is not confident in or that is too contentious. So the cheap default judge resolves the clear cases and bows out of the hard ones, spending scarce smart-agent and human attention only where it is genuinely needed; the psyche is the highest-authority and lowest-availability adjudicator. This is the architectural expression of intent-is-primordial: when a contract or a judge cannot or should not decide, it defers upward, ultimately to the human. Reaching the psyche adjudicator depends on a psyche-facing UI: until that UI exists the EscalateToPsyche outcome is intentionally an inert dead-letter and not a defect, because the terminal human rung is gated on the interface that lets a psyche receive and answer escalations.] Zero Minimum Zero [criome])) (ggvg ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Decision [|The CriomOS VM-testing node feature should be reachable via a Criome domain such as vm-testing.<cluster>.criome (name illustrative), so the test VM's display, console, or harness is addressable by name across the cluster. Integrates with the domain-criome registry and resolution plus cluster networking. Extends record 2630. *distributed systems*|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (givl ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Principle [Cloud signal language starts small and typed] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (glr2 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [NOTA always corresponds to a specified object. The goal is that when NOTA-as-schema specifies the objects themselves, the correspondence chain runs all the way down — schema is data, schema specifies data types, schema-emitted Rust gives objects their shape, and operating on those objects through SEMA can itself edit the schema.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (gm3a ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [The schema root should be represented faithfully as positional structs: an imports/exports struct for what the schema consumes and shares, and an input/output struct for the channel surface, using square brackets because structs are ordered field vectors.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (gmlv ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Principle [Schema-created base enums define the reaction and action types an actor can receive and emit; execution matches those schema variants to select replies and route work.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (gnfx ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Constraint [Large model prefetches on Prometheus should run as durable target-side systemd work with a target-side periodic monitor, so progress checks do not depend on the operator's local SSH session staying alive.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (go8m ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [Spirit intent-resolution operations are typed combined actions so the thinker resolves a guardian verdict in one atomic call; there should be several such actions, the simplest being adding a new record while deprecating a list of existing records referred to by identifier *transactions*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (goty ([(Technology (Software (Security Privacy)))] Decision [A private-record shorthand should lower to a normal Spirit record with an elevated privacy magnitude, while ordinary simple record shorthands default to open public privacy.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (gq9p ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [PeerCheck retired; signal-version-handover is the single discovery mechanism for n