an replacing forge] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hfvl ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [|Typed-data-tree vocabulary: branches and leaves. The workspace's typed records (structs and enums in the sema database) form trees of branches and leaves. A LEAF is a fixed-size terminal — typically an enum of unit variants only (Bool as True/False; Magnitude's 7 unit variants; Kind's five-kind taxonomy). Final leaves have no variable size. A BRANCH carries variable-size or data-carrying content — vectors, data-carrying enum variants, structs containing variable-size members. Branches are themselves trees (recursive). A vector is a kind of dynamic-leaf in one reading (single field at one position) but practically a branch because it points into another tree or series of trees. A data-carrying enum variant is a branch because the variant's payload doesn't fit as a single tree node. Adopt this vocabulary going forward in design conversations and skill files.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hg6k ([(Work Productivity)] Correction [In an active troubleshooting task where the user asked for a working connection, the agent should not stop at diagnosis when the next step is a narrow safe fix; it should apply the fix and then report the result.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hh3z ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems))) (Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Decision [|A type's kind is announced by the delimiter that wraps its value, the same way a brace body means struct and a square-bracket body means enum. Generics use the reserved pipe-parenthesis delimiter (| ... |), pipes inside, mirroring the existing pipe-text string delimiter. A generic declaration is Name (| [params] body |): the pipe-parenthesis marks the type generic, the params are the binder list, and the body is an ordinary struct or enum body nested inside. This assigns meaning to one of the two reserved pipe-bracket extension points named by j9du; nota-next already parses these blocks (PipeParenthesis and PipeBrace delimiters exist), so it is schema-level work, not a seed-parser change. Realizes j9du and satisfies 3742.|] Zero Minimum Zero [nota nota-next schema-next])) (hh9p ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Correction [|Enum variants cannot be declared without an enum type name. A parenthesized list such as ((Parse Expression) (Render Expression)) has no enum type name for the outer list, so it is not a valid enum declaration surface. Any enum declaration must name the enum type; variant tags such as Parse and Render only make sense inside that named enum declaration.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hhaf ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Correction [Known-root NOTA serialization must not be implemented as ad hoc field string joins on each schema object. A file read as a known root type is already the root body; the NOTA layer should expose an object/body parsing and encoding abstraction that reads and writes the ordered fields of the known type.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hnog ([(Technology (Software (Programming Parsing)))] Correction [After NOTA structural parsing matches a file body or a delimited object, the next semantic parsing step should receive the matched body's inner object stream rather than the outer delimiter wrapper. Known-root files and matched delimited objects share the same body abstraction: the expected type decides whether the body is read as a struct, vector, enum variant, or other value.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hnsn ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [Schema field names are inferred from type names in field position] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hp3r ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [Production Spirit does not need an immediate weight-field migration; weight belongs in the future record-shape design until the mechanism is settled.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (hr3z ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Principle [capability-missing daemons may eventually