ation shape: CollectRemovalCandidates is a single COMBINED guarded operation, not an emit-only extraction that leaves destruction to a separate Remove. It archives the Zero-certainty candidates and then retracts them in one call, with archive-first safety — if archiving fails nothing is retracted and the affected candidates return archive-failed. The discovery-versus-destruction separation 3v3r sought is preserved inside the one operation, archive preceding retract, rather than by splitting into two operation roots. This matches the deployed behavior and record o70j which archives before removal.] Zero Minimum Zero [spirit])) (js59 ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [Design reports for schema-driven component work should show what the schema produces: REST code, typed interfaces, derived traits, implementations, and the derivation boundaries where flaws or improvements can be spotted.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (jvpe ([(Technology (Software (Engineering ApplicationProgrammingInterfaces)))] Principle [Cloud provider support should be build-selectable; unsupported provider requests return a typed unsupported-capability reply, with future self-upgrade possible when support is cheaply available.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (jwgm ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [The Spirit observation mode named DescriptionOnly is misleading when the reply includes record identifier, topic, kind, description, and magnitude rather than only descriptions. The mode name or reply shape should be corrected so the name matches the data.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (jwmf ([(Information Documentation)] Decision [|Report filename convention is reports/<role>/<N>-<Variant>-<topic>-<date>.md where <Variant> is a capitalized word naming the report kind. Every report has a variant. Variants are in the filename not in a separate directory; reports stay in their lane subdirectory (reports/designer/ reports/operator/ etc). Proposed variant set covers main scenar