gn default is quorum authorization for meaningful objects and trust-crossing state. Time-driven pulses are not an ambient global heartbeat. A heartbeat is programmed by accepting a contract with an after-time condition: that acceptance schedules a later check of the contract against related events; when the crystallized time condition matures, criome checks whether the relevant events happened, and if they did not, it triggers a new acceptance for the time-based condition's resulting state, to be quorum-signed. Criome keeps no operational delivery registry; any criome-local subscription surface is observation and audit only, with the direct criome-to-criome agreement lane the sole non-router message path.] Zero Minimum Zero [criome router])) (maeq ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [Signal-frame itself should also be represented as schema; the frame kernel is not exempt from the schema-as-architecture rule.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (mazv ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Decision [|The engine target running state is a live orchestrated system: persona - the manager and supervisor of the whole thing - runs and supervises the introspector (persona-introspect), the schema daemon, and the other triad components together as one running orchestrated whole, not just proven in-tree. Moving toward this running orchestrated system is the direction for engine-forward effort. *orchestration*|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (mchq ([(Technology (Software (Programming TypeSystems)))] Decision [|Divergent field names like field certainty of type Magnitude are achieved by declaring a NEWTYPE giving the type its specific name (Certainty (Magnitude)). Then the schema uses (Certainty) in the field position; the field name derives from Certainty as lowercased certainty. No per-field renaming syntax. If you want a more specific name use a longer/different type name not a per-position override.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (mcwa ([(Technology (Software E