ce objects] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (s60q ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [|The double-implementation strategy provides COMPARISON as the integration mechanism. Operator and designer arrive at the same problem from different angles - operator from concrete amalgamation of existing prototypes; designer from forward-looking iteration. Where they converge is signal that the design is settling. Where they diverge surfaces unresolved questions for psyche review. The strategy mitigates single-track drift (one agent inferring without challenge) by structurally requiring two angles.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (s6hg ([(Safety Privacy)] Constraint [Private information must not leak into public reports or other ordinary public workspace surfaces when multiple agents are working in the workspace.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (s8es ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Decision [SubscribePolicy default is TerminateAtHandover - active subscriptions cleanly terminate at the handover boundary; clients reconnect to next] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (sdgj ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [|Schema struct fields per component (in order): optional metadata/imports section first, then three short-header definitions (regular signal header, owner signal header, sema operation header), then namespace map, possibly with a final extension vector of optional-fields. Each header is represented as a vector of variants. The schema struct itself is defined in the schema-library base schema.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (sg4o ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Correction [CLI examples and agent instructions should wrap inline NOTA in shell double quotes; the bracket-string notation exists so NOTA itself avoids double quotes and the whole NOTA object can be passed as one double-quoted shell argument.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (st16 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Correction [Ope