d record only the name of the object being activated; the macro-generated interface already has that object name, so trace should not carry rich payload snapshots for each boundary.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (t2lh ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Correction [Spirit-facing skills must document the current production Spirit version and record shape so agents do not keep calling stale versioned wrappers such as spirit-v0.2.0 directly after the production cutover.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (t312 ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [|The 64-bit signal namespace is partitioned into a system-types zone (SignalCore) and a component-specific-types zone, with pre-allocated zone sizes. Repartitioning the allocation between zones is a major version event with backward-compatibility implications.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (t3hd ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [|Schema files use the .schema file extension; file extension supplies the type. NO outer parentheses wrapping the schema struct — fields appear directly in the file without any wrapping record. Designer 326-v3 section 2.1 outer (...) wrapper is wrong because file context already says this is a schema.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (t3l4 ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Constraint [Schema-derived Rust emission must not rewire into the old signal macro implementation.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (t6s1 ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Correction [Typed NOTA projection should not introduce redundant wrapper delimiters when the enclosing head already determines the positional payload shape; operation roots should render their payload fields directly where the schema shape is unambiguous.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (t85k ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [The structural macro node grammar is itself schema-expressible, so it can be made self-describing. A structural macro node is a constructor that takes a typed and counted set of objects, so its shape vocabulary can be specified in schema and each concrete macro definition written as NOTA data conforming to that spec, instead of hand-coded as a Rust shape derive. Then the layer that decodes NOTA would itself be defined in NOTA. This points to building that schema specification for the structural macro node.] Zero Minimum Zero [nota-next schema-next])) (ta58 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [Denied schema syntax patterns must not resurface as current examples; agents should use the latest accepted schema syntax when sketching schemas and treat older parenthesized variant-list examples as stale unless explicitly marked legacy.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (td4h ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Modularity)))] Clarification [|The schema type library (the macro substrate) MAY live in a separate repo from the schema component daemon if separation works better organizationally. Two possible shapes: (i) co-located — schema component triad holds daemon + the schema-types library in the same repo; (ii) separated — a dedicated schema-types library repo distinct from the schema component triad, both consuming the same compiled NOTA schema artifacts. Lean unsettled; depends on whether the library carries a meaningfully different release cadence from the daemon, and whether other consumers of the library would prefer to depend on a small library crate rather than pulling in the triad scaffolding. The compiled schema artifact (binary form per spirit 398) is the same in both shapes; only the crate-layout differs.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (th8a ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Future Spirit expansion should use spirit-next as design inspiration while tying together the richer data already present in production Spirit.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (tj99 ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Decision [|Evolve the schema-rust-next daemon emitter (with triad-runtime) to host lojix load-bearing daemon properties so concurrent daemons adopt the GENERATED daemon rather than keeping hand-written forks: BoundedWorkers concurrent serving with a fresh per-request engine over a shared store, a two-wire-contract single-Nexus-root working tier where the owner meta tier is a first-class typed engine path rather than a raw escape hatch, and the per-request frame-size and read-timeout hardening bounds in the generated transport. lojix hand-written daemon is the reference implementation feeding back into the emitter.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (tkou ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Constraint [domain-criome runtime excludes provider APIs and direct CLI store access] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (tq18 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Clarification [|In the running-orchestrated-system goal (mazv), Orchestrate refers to the orchestrate COMPONENT - the orchestration component runtime, repo /git/github.com/LiGoldragon/orchestrate - not the act of orchestrating. The orchestrate component runs the set of component daemons: persona (the manager of the whole thing), the introspector, the schema daemon, and the others. persona is the engine manager; orchestrate is the runtime that runs them together.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (trvl ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [Design work progresses by proving one prototype capability at a time in a worktree — pick the next thing the schema-stack prototype needs to prove, prove it in a feature branch worktree, integrate, then move to the next. Avoid breadth-first design fan-out; depth-first single-capability proving keeps the design grounded in working code] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (tve6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [For CriomOS-home dictation and desktop audio, keep reliable laptop-microphone fallback and avoid a hard DJI hot-loop dependency; prefer the connected DJI Bluetooth microphone through system audio default-source policy rather than a Whisrs-specific wrapper. A DJI keep-alive may exist only as a sidecar consumer of the real DJI microphone source, keeping that mic awake without becoming the source selected by the system or Whisrs.] Zero Minimum Zero [CriomOS-home DJI-mic Whisrs])) (twb4 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Constraint [Architecture presentations should use short focused graphs with readable text, split large system explanations into several report parts, and pair each important visual with real code from the implementation.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ty24 ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Decision [|domain-criome is the authority for .criome domains; each .criome domain (e.g. goldragon.criome) is its own authority server, content-addressable. To check the current authority for a domain, ask the domain's own daemon. Last-snapshot per domain serves as cached state. This gives the workspace its own content-addressed DNS. *networking*|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (tymh ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [Plain PascalCase tokens are unit variants.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (tz5j ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Decision [Orchestrate should become the production replacement for the current agent orchestration helper by using the new triad/runtime crate logic rather than deepening the transitional helper.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (tzp3 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [Schema imports should use explicit import variants rather than an opaque Path variant with optional selection.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (u0ik ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [Schema variants can be ordinary vectors OR macros that bring their own schema-reading logic. Macros use NOTA format but customize interpretation by structural SHAPE - curly-bracket with single identifier, curly-bracket with even count of items where all key positions resolve to consistent type, etc. Each macro definition carries 