e cluster so the browser-driving model runs inside our infrastructure.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (u2s9 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [Spirit entry weight is intended as a set record axis, not only a computed search score: agglomerating several related intents into one record should preserve their accumulated importance through a higher weight, because after compaction the source mentions are no longer visible as separate active records. This weight-field design is low-certainty and should be revisited before production implementation.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (u47i ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [Engine operations should expose tree-to-tree and enum-to-enum matching surfaces.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (u71r ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|Refined 64-bit signal type structure: byte 0 is the ROOT VERB (the most universal quality, beingness of the object — e.g. Help, Query, Message); bytes 1-7 are 7 data-carrying sub-variants forming the verb namespace. 8 enums total: 1 root + 7 sub. The verb-space is itself a single enum. Macro standardizes the verb-at-root pattern. Verb chosen as load-bearing root because verbs unify across namespaces *encoding*|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (u8od ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Schema is the growing focus of the workspace; the psyche wants to deeply understand schema from every angle — backward and forward, inside and outside. Both operator and designer keep producing reports that concretely show schema in action: what goes into the schema, what comes out, and what code the schema creates, in the this-code-creates-this-code form, with the implementation — repeatedly, as an ongoing discipline.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ublb ([(Technology (Software (Engineering ApplicationProgrammingInterfaces)))] Clarification [gap-fill on the directive operator received - the schema-emitted data types are positioned as REST-shaped at the wire layer; the psyche said the data type REST is emitted by this schema system and the single-owner system mirrors the REST concept; this frames the wire protocol architecturally as REST where schema defines the resource/message types and the single-owner state-of-record property mirrors RESTs stateless-server-with-canonical-state semantics; operators record 945 captures schema-creates-actor-enums and 947 captures schema-objects-as-method-surface but the explicit REST architectural framing is implicit; this gap-fill makes the framing explicit so future agents see REST as the wire architecture pattern not just data-type-emission] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ucqp ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Schema namespaces can import local type namespaces from other schemas] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ue6x ([(Technology (Software (Data Persistence)))] Principle [Component data lifecycle should prefer explicit archival lowering before hard deletion: stale or low-certainty data is marked and moved out of the hot working database to keep runtime state manageable, while recoverability is best-effort rather than guaranteed unless a stronger retention class says otherwise.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ue7r ([(Technology (Software (Observability Tracing)))] Constraint [Do not enable tracing on the tracing interface itself for now; trace enablement should be controlled per crate or component so the trace system does not recursively trace its own trace events.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (uhz9 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Clarification [Schema is the composability and programmability layer on top of NOTA: it turns NOTA into a system for describing composable data types and data-driven behavior, programmable by the user to create new interfaces for specialized engine behavior expressed as a node-graph data type. Schemas nest: an engine may contain sub-engines, each with its own schema and interface, so signal, nexus, and sema are the three top schemas but internal sub-behaviors get their own. The namespace mirrors Rust modules: one file with fully-qualified colon-separated names, or split into files like Rust modules, importable and re-exportable. A schema is a key-value struct at the top whose entries declare the module public symbols. Imports are a key-value map of module name to a data-carrying variant naming the import KIND such as import-all, from-git, from-path, adjacent-directory, same-directory, or from-repository-root, so the import system is modular across scenarios.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ui5d ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Management)))] Correction [Do work properly or not at all — stop burning psyche tokens on half-assed slop. Do not dispatch underspecified or wrong-shaped subagent work that produces garbage, such as the string-keyed consumption-only VmTesting hack instead of the typed end-to-end pipeline. Either specify and execute the work correctly with proper oversight and verification, or do not start it. Delegating a flawed brief and then surfacing the gap as if the work were acceptable wastes the psyche's tokens and attention.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (up9q ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Decision [A lojix deploy or build survives client disconnect. A durable deploy is owned by a job actor that owns the external process and persists job state, reporting status later — the process lifetime is not coupled to the request stream. Cancellation is declared per operation in schema: durable deploys survive disconnect by default; speculative queries or builds may opt into kill-on-drop. No blanket kill-on-drop on effect processes.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (upuf ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Management)))] Decision [The system-specialist role is being renamed to system-operator; the report directory and orchestration protocol should use system-operator.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (uqoi ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [The header declaration is a vector of ordered enum variants.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (uti9 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [|The schema-schema is implemented as core Rust code - the macro interface. It exposes what other macros build on. The macro interface defines the different inputs and what they are called (a macros input type IS its name in the macro). People build their own macros against this core interface.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (utyl ([(Information Curation)] Principle [Agents should track intent cut position and hot topic windows] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (uuu9 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Principle [Assembled schema should make names globally unambiguous by context] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ux4w ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Principle [|rkyv's natural storage layout uses a larger namespace than the data strictly needs (a bool occupies a byte; a small-variant enum's discriminator fits within a byte even when there are only 2-3 active variants). This headroom enables a class of zero-cost schema changes that require no data migration whatsoever: adding a fourth unit variant to a three-variant enum that still fits in the byte. Constraint: variant order must be preserved (existing payload bytes must still decode under the new schema). The schema-layout schema must expose this headroom (e.g., declared discriminator width) so the migration-derivation step can identify zero-cost changes and skip the migration step. Other zero-cost-class candidates: adding fields at the end of a struct under append-only encoding; widening fixed-width integer fields where rkyv reserves space.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (uxiz ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Clarification [Single-object sigil sugar is an open macro-node design frontier: a leading sigil can eventually make one NOTA object stand for a larger pair or field expression when the sigil makes the intended macro case obvious. This is exploratory and must be represented 