ntSystems)))] Principle [Operator should become a more targeted trained Persona role] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (v91q ([(Technology (Software (Distributed EventDrivenArchitecture)))] Principle [|Actor execution produces FAN-OUT outputs. When an interaction actor decides an outcome, it emits multiple things in parallel: execution effects, responses returned to the originating actors, AND additional messages dispatched to other actors (typical: send a mutation message to the database actor, send a notification message to the subscription actor, return a reply to the requester - all from one interaction-actor decision). Single-input-multiple-output is the normal shape; the actor never produces just one thing. The schema encodes the fan-out outputs declaratively - per interact-trait variant, the set of possible outputs is fixed and closed.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (veqq ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Principle [|The update mechanism (sema-upgrade) is a structural prerequisite for any deployed persona component. The deploy → restart → update flow means a daemon coming up against an existing redb must either find no schema drift (no migration needed) or have a migration path through sema-upgrade. Without that path, any contract edit after first deploy breaks the next restart. The implication for getting mind + orchestrate deployed: their schema must be stable enough OR sema-upgrade must cover their migration before deployment, or the operator must be willing to drop-and-rebuild on every contract edit until sema-upgrade catches them.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (vhs2 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture))) (Technology (Software (Security Authentication))) (Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [Criome's internal language is a limited typed policy language over public-key identity atoms - NOT a general-purpose virtual machine - drawing its limited-operation discipline from the constrained VMs of Ethereum, Tezos, and Solana. Public keys are the atomic unit of identity; above them it composes complex identity contracts from signature and time-lock mechanics: signature quorums of k-of-n form and thresholds that increase or decrease over elapsed time. It carries explicit divergence-reconciliation objects for when two networks split and how the reconciliation is determined, where conflict resolution may be mediated by an LLM-oracle call to a provider which itself resolves through one of those identity contracts - for example a paid expert panel adjudicating the fairest resolution model. This is criome's Nexus object and verb vocabulary, the objects and operations the identity world treats, to be researched, defined in schema, and prototyped.] Zero Minimum Zero [criome Nexus])) (vnnx ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [|The schema-derived cloud port uses TWO schemas — signal-cloud.schema (working, peer-callable, read-only Observe and Validate) and meta-signal-cloud.schema (policy, owner-only, the eight account and plan mutations) — each emitting its own Signal Nexus SEMA engines and sharing record types, with the cloud runtime crate importing both and running two listeners. This follows the existing two-contract triad shape (two authority surfaces, two sockets, two listener actors) and supersedes the single cloud schema target in cloud ARCHITECTURE.md. Psyche-chosen 2026-06-04.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (vpa5 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Decision [The nota-related logic for the new schema-derived stack lands on a nota-next BRANCH on the existing nota repository rather than a new repo. Per psyche: I think the logic in Nota is going to change. I mean, or we use a branch. Call it Nota Next. The branch is the chosen direction; nota repo keeps its current name.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (vpp2 ([(Technology (Software (Security Privacy)))] Decision [Infrastructure-improvement intent is not private by default; privacy classification should separate