language should be specified by its own schema file.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (w2g3 ([(Technology (Software (Security Authentication))) (Technology (Software (Security Authorization)))] Decision [Spirit should be an early pilot consumer of Criome-backed operation authorization: Spirit operations that require authentication ask Criome to authorize an exact content-addressed request or log-message digest, with the concrete envelope design still open.] Zero Minimum Zero [spirit criome])) (w9gq ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [|Every schema file is loaded with a default schema attached implicitly - the schema-schema. The schema-schema defines the structural shape expected for schema files (root struct + sections). It is the lowest-level macro primitive everything else builds on.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (waz6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Decision [|Default behavior — when something changes in context that would correct a fresh-in-context report (a report the agent just wrote or is actively engaged with), the agent EDITS the report directly rather than narrating I should edit this report. Action over narration. Applies whenever the correction is clearly indicated by something in the conversation and the report is fresh enough that the agent still holds its context.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wb2k ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [DeepSeek-as-library subsumed into persona-pi triad; no separate deepseek wrapping component] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wdhw ([(Technology (Software (Engineering DevelopmentProcess)))] Principle [Refresh intent before maintenance or implementation] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wdri ([(Technology (Software (Operations ReleaseEngineering)))] Decision [Cloud component production push prioritized; first MVP can skip new schema-engine approach to ship faster] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wfdt ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [The schema substrate should self-host its own definition types, generating schema-next macro-table types from core.schema rather than hand-writing them in declarative.rs, as the deliberately chosen proving first step of progressively absorbing Rust type surface into schema. Macros-as-data already works, and the next move is the types that decode it becoming schema-derived too.] Zero Minimum Zero [schema-next nota-next])) (whr2 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Decision [|Schema language has a lowering executor — a recursive parser walks the NOTA schema tree and dispatches at each node based on bracket/paren shape, lowering the transient sugar form into a fully-specced canonical form. The dispatch rules: bare identifier = reference to namespace entry (resolved by lookup); square bracket vector = enum declaration with variants; single-paren single-identifier = newtype tuple wrapping the named type; multi-element parens = struct with positional fields; (fieldname [variants]) = inline enum field with explicit name. The executor assembles the full schema by resolving paths and references.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wipc ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [Schema headers are enum namespace nodes, not one payload pair per verb.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wiq2 ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Principle [The basic schema-emitted type definitions should derive NOTA traits and rkyv traits from the same data objects. Additional communication traits belong on the generated schema root objects when those objects cross component boundaries.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wqi2 ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Correction [|Root struct positional fields are bare — no Name@ prefix. The universal Name@Delimiter rule (record 1216) applies to DECLARATIONS where the user invents a new type name, not to positional values at the root struct's known fields. A .schema file's root is a struct with fixed positional fields (imports / input / output / namespace per the schema-of-schemas); the value at each field is bare — empty-brace imports, [Record@Entry Observe@Query ...] input enum variants, [RecordAccepted@... ...] output variants, brace-namespace declarations. Same treatment bare {} for imports and bare { ... } for the namespace already had; Input/Output need the same treatment because they are the same kind of thing — values at positional root-struct slots, not user declarations. Additional plane roots (NexusInput, NexusOutput, SemaInput, SemaOutput) declared INSIDE the namespace stay as Name@[...] because they ARE user declarations. Corrects the 1216 carve-out that named Input, Output, and plane roots together as needing Name@: top-level Input/Output are positional values, not declarations. Per psyche 2026-05-30 against report 429 §5a.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wr8s ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Modularity)))] Decision [Crate name for the VersionProjection home is version-projection, peer to signal-sema] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wsgh ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Clarification [MigrationIndex is a runtime decoder lookup] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wtaz ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [Vector sugar is structurally a single-field container object] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wv7w ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Principle [Schema diffs should be isolated as typed upgrade operations.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wvrt ([(Work Productivity)] Decision [After active implementation/prototype subagent work, run context maintenance and a fresh-intent audit over recent reports and code before deciding what to address immediately. The main operator should synthesize the returned work, choose sensible immediate fixes, and implement them rather than letting stale context drive the next slice.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wxip ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Principle [Help and documentation should be schema data in a mirror description namespace over the global symbol namespace, with generated defaults when no explicit description entry exists for a fully qualified symbol.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wy3j ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Principle [NOTA shape can project through front matter formats] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (wywp ([(Work Teamwork)] Principle [For large schema implementation and synthesis tasks, the operator should use subagents in parallel when explicitly authorized, with the main agent staying responsible for integration, constraints, tests, and the final report.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (x020 ([(Technology (Software (Data Formats)))] Correction [A single string that qualifies as a symbol name must be encoded in NOTA as a bare symbol, not quoted with brackets. Bracket strings are not the representation for schema names that are symbol-safe.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (x2su ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [input and output are PARTITIONS of a single enum tag space - not two separate independent enums but two halves of one tag namespace at the wire level; the conceptual split for a 1-byte enum carrying ~240 slots is approximately two-thirds: first ~120 slots reserved for INPUT variants, slots ~121 to ~240 reserved for OUTPUT variants; this means at the wire byte level a single tag byte identifies BOTH the variant and whether the message is an input or output by which range it falls in; the schema author declares Input and Output separately at the schema level but the rkyv-compiled binary form merges them into one tag space; this is also the conceptual basis for the structural header at the message layer - first byte tells you immediately whether to dispatch on input handlers or output handlers; the specific 240-slot 120-120 split is illustrative not locked - larger enums get larger spaces *encoding*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (x4tx ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|Three-tier signal type sizing: (1) 64-bit micro-message — the default auto-loggable variant every Signal Operation/Reply/Effect/SemaObservation implements via macro, packing root variant tag plus packed sub-discriminators into a u64; (2) 64-byte summary message — hand-implemented when a type has natural summary fields (public key + metadata, short string, etc.) — basis for a second subscription tier; (3) full unrestricted message — current rkyv-encoded records. Variant always at the root. Macro autogens tier 1 trait. Research needed on what fits in 64 bits and 64 bytes plus storage/logging efficiency|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (x5b7 ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Decision [Spirit exposes version lookup as the bare NOTA input Version, invoked as spirit Version, not as a Unix flag and not as a parenthesized empty record.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (x83q ([(Language Terminology)] Clarification [Whole workspace stack is named 'the Criome stack'; 'Persona engine' is the more specific term for the AI-work part of the stack] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (x88n ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [|Schema field names and type names are unified — in a struct, each fields identity IS the type name. Field appears lowercase (camelCase derived from PascalCase) in code; type stays PascalCase. Example: in struct Entry, a Kind reference becomes field name kind (lowercase) with type Kind (PascalCase). Same identifier expressed once, lowered to two casings by context.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xayx ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Clarification [Schema builtin lowering components are macro-variant lowerers at node-definition points.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xc2d ([(Technology (Software (Engineering VersionControl)))] Decision [The operator-created main branch in each new replacement repository should start as an amalgamation of the strongest prior prototype ideas; designer worktrees branch from that concept-prototype amalgamation baseline.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xfc5 ([(Technology (Software (Data Migration)))] Correction [Spirit hash-identity migration should not keep numeric record lookup behavior alive; it should create a migration table mapping hash identities to former ordinal numeric identifiers, while the live lookup surface moves to hash identity.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xfhu ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Correction [Top-level schema is not a flat vector of same-kind declarations] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xi3g ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Correction [Open-work and psyche reports must explain opaque unresolved items in plain terms, including what the item means and why it matters; listing a label without explanation is not enough.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xq4z ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [Nexus input and Nexus output must not be modeled as symmetric lists of the same operation categories. Nexus input is what Nexus receives as facts/replies/events to decide from; Nexus output is what Nexus commands or emits next. If both sides list Signal and SEMA operations in the same-looking way, the interface loses meaning and reads as nonsense.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xsp1 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Parsing)))] Decision [Schema should be able to act as its own codec for its shorthand authored form, so shorthand schema syntax round-trips as typed schema data rather than being only a one-way parser convenience.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xv4a ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Design)))] Principle [When design questions are numerous, propose intent-pattern leans and mark uncertainty] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xv9v ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Constraint [Prometheus deploys should use the safe BootOnce path rather than Switch until console/out-of-band access and sign-off are in place; avoid leaving an unverified generation staged for the next reboot unless deliberately accepted.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xxgp ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Clarification [tests illustrate design when named as the invariant they prove. one concept per test. short inline fixtures. assertion exposing the key design point. PATTERN comment at top naming the invariant. derived from nota-next schema-next style. requested for pattern-a pilot tests on worktree report 401.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (xzlv ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Clarification [|The signal/nexus/sema-bearing schema should be called a REACTIVE SCHEMA. Analogy to Nix: derivation is the built-in primitive, and higher-level builders extend it; likewise the plain SCHEMA is the primitive that specifies data types (the shapes), and the REACTIVE SCHEMA is the extension that adds the reaction surface (signal in, nexus through, sema state, output back). Plain schema says what data IS; reactive schema says how data MOVES. Most schemas are plain; a component top-level schema is reactive. Naming proposed by the psyche; pending the schema-syntax design conversation settling.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y0m6 ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Management)))] Decision [|Rename the system-assistant lane to system-designer — a specialized designer lane for system topics (CriomOS, horizon, lojix, goldragon, deployment), parallel to nota-designer. Reports dir renames reports/system-assistant → reports/system-designer; lock renames orchestrate/system-assistant.lock → orchestrate/system-designer.lock; roles.list adds system-designer and retires system-assistant. The role inherits designer discipline (full required-reading list, structural authority on its surface) with system as its specialization scope.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y0vr ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [|There is no composite intent type in code - composite and agglomeration are a language and behavior concept for expressing an idea, not a record type or variant. This refines the earlier composite-record direction (Principle audg3): provenance and agglomeration are expressed through a relations field on records, not a dedicated Composite type. Refreshing several intents need not produce one merged record - it may produce two or three records of different kinds.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y11g ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Constraint [Imported schema names must not collide in one context] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y1g8 ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [The root schema must itself be described by an explicit schema object. The .schema reader may know that it is reading the root Schema type, but the Schema type still needs a concrete schema description of its own fields and nested definitions.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y1n5 ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Decision [Schema macro handlers receive NotaBody body streams and should not receive wrapper delimiters. Macro matching strips the outer delimiter before handing the inner body to the next semantic step.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y3tc ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [Generated modules may mirror schema-file contexts to avoid name clashes] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y88n ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [The contract-daemon and engine-stack split should have Spirit as a proper exemplar; Spirit must not be left as an all-in-one pilot that agents describe as an explicitly non-copyable shape.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (y94z ([(Technology (Software (Security SecretsManagement)))] Decision [The workspace skills must state the secret-handling discipline explicitly: gopass wrapping of environment variables, sops-nix cluster secret storage, and the never-show-a-secret rule, so every agent applies it the same way.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (yivn ([(Technology (Software (Operations Deployment)))] Correction [Do not run live Home activation or Niri/desktop-affecting deployment in an active session with ongoing agents unless the user explicitly confirms the disruption window. Desktop deploy work must preserve active agent sessions and must not log the user out or restart the session unexpectedly.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (yjik ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Clarification [Signal repositories carry only the signal schema for their wire vocabulary; non-signal schema for runtime planes, storage, provider effects, REST surfaces, or broader component behavior belongs in the runtime component or the appropriate schema/runtime repository, not in the signal repository.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (yjvy ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|Signal root-level macro composition emits 64-bit super-tiny message headers. The 64 bits encode root type plus variant kind (data-carrying or unit) plus type info sufficient to discriminate any object in the namespace; object recognition is constant-time on the header. Every signal contract macro emits headers matching exactly this namespace shape.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (yn6g ([(Technology (Software Observability))] Decision [Testing-mode logging should be configured by typed NOTA configuration data. In a testing build, the CLI can act as or attach to the log surface so a test run receives structured interface-use logs while exercising the normal binary protocol path. *logging*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (yntp ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Constraint [Schema input/output inline declarations should stay shallow: use inline root payload bodies for the operation-level shape, but move deeper reusable or nested structure into named namespace types rather than burying full trees inside the root vectors.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ypde ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Documentation)))] Constraint [Schema macro examples must be large working examples used by current tests, not tiny sketches. Structural macro positions are places where schema expects macro expansion; those examples must show where structural macros appear, how named @ macros appear, and how the schema reader uses those forms now.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (yrsm ([(Technology (Software (Programming Compilation)))] Clarification [Schema node values lower by context] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (yvez ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Decision [The schema Rust emission should split Signal Nexus and SEMA into separate emitted namespaces now, so plane payloads can use simple names like Input and Output inside their plane namespace instead of carrying redundant plane prefixes.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (z1yz ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Constraint [Schema must have a schema-authored self-description even while the bootstrap Rust reader remains hand-written. The schema file that defines how to read schema files is required as a tested artifact: it does not have to be load-bearing for the reader yet, but it must lower through the current engine and expose the root Schema shape and nested declaration types clearly.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (z2ge ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Management)))] Decision [Assistant and counselor report work should live in private role-specific repositories rather than the public primary report tree; each role gets its own private repository and commits its own reports there.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (z2nx ([(Technology (Software (Programming Macros)))] Principle [Gap-fill from forwarded designer prompt: NOTA itself should have a schema; over time the behavior of NOTA and the Rust code generated around it should be schema-derived rather than hand-maintained as a separate parser island.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (z550 ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Decision [Schema and Spirit should move toward a runtime-upgradable schema system: schema changes are represented as typed upgrade objects, and Rust generation emits upgrade and compatibility code from those objects so new generated components can accept previous schema/data/message shapes through explicit typed upgrade paths.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (z5aw ([(Technology (Software (Operations BuildSystem)))] Principle [Future forge build logic may let generated Rust code become content-addressed crates directly, reducing the need for separate generated-code repositories once forge can own that build path outside Nix.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (z8gj ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Clarification [|The schema component exposes a schema type library — types that other crates import to reference schema metadata. The library is the build-time substrate consumed by macros (the signal-side macro plus the symmetric sema-side macro per spirit 390). Three faces of the schema component: (1) Runtime daemon — serves short-header to schema lookups; (2) Library crate — exposes the schema types other crates import; (3) Macro substrate — the library is what the signal/sema macros consume when generating code from a NOTA schema input (per spirit 391). The library is the build-time face; the daemon is the runtime face; both stem from the same NOTA schema source.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zbuy ([(Technology (Software (Distributed ProtocolDesign)))] Decision [Guardian model performs semantic judgment for every guarded write; deterministic code gathers context, validates structure, and applies typed verdict consequences. *admission control*] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zcuv ([(Technology (Software (Programming Grammars)))] Correction [Schema source shape drops outer wrapper and uses header-first sections] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zf4v ([(Technology (Software (Data Migration)))] Decision [|Upgrade mechanism: (1) schema changes between versions; (2) schema-diff identifies what moved/changed/dropped/renamed; (3) hand-written Rust bridge code per version-boundary handles the moved or transformed data types; (4) version number marks the boundary - sets which schema applies; (5) the new daemon is recompiled with the previous schema also available for reference; (6) auto-migration on database load - daemon reads DB version marker; if DB is on previous (main, in next/main/previous vocab per rec 672) version, the migration method runs once, transforms all data to the new shape, updates the version marker, persists the new database. Assembled schemas can potentially be stored to enable efficient diffing.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zk6y ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Correction [Schema-emitted Signal, Nexus, and SEMA engines are kameo actors, not synchronous method spines driven by a runner loop over mutex-wrapped state. Actors everywhere is the architecture; the generated triad daemons are not exempt. Deferring advanced runtime machinery — backpressure, scheduling, the runtime-control trait surface — never meant deferring actors or emitting synchronous daemons. A minimal kameo actor carrying on_start and on_stop adopts kameo now while that deeper machinery stays deferred. The current synchronous daemon emission with mutex-wrapped engine state is drift to correct, not a sanctioned end state.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zm8n ([(Technology (Software (Engineering ApplicationProgrammingInterfaces)))] Decision [Provider integrations may be build-time opt-ins, and capability observation must distinguish built-but-unconfigured providers from providers not built into the daemon.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zocz ([(Technology (Software (Security SecretsManagement)))] Constraint [Agents may inspect authentication tokens and other secret values when the task requires plaintext access authorized by the psyche or by an existing workspace task. Visible plaintext is transient working material: keep it out of chat, reports, logs, commits, argv, shell traces, the Nix store, test fixtures, and checked-in files; prefer blind pipe-to-sink handling when it is enough; when inspection is needed, minimize exposure and move the value directly to the requested consumer or encrypted store.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zs9c ([(Technology (Software (Programming CodeGeneration)))] Principle [The assembled schema tree is the complete input to Rust generation, including code to read and write NOTA text and portable rkyv binary data for SEMA and signal formats; Rust emission may later be invoked from a single macro that reads repository schema files.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zste ([(Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Principle [Every engine should have an object that owns the logic it runs, with daemon startup and transport boilerplate pushed behind libraries or macros.] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (zt9i ([(Technology (Software (Programming DomainSpecificLanguages)))] Correction [|The aski-core (and its successor askic / askicc) pattern is an analog past experience, not the foundation to replicate. The earlier design intent there was a more beautiful syntax to represent Rust; the persona-component schema work is an entirely different goal. The new direction is a dedicated schema specification language akin to Cap'n Proto schema files but more explicit, scoped only to the workspace's Rust subset (no tuples, since the workspace treats tuples as poorly-defined structs). Reading aski-core and askicc as foundational substrate for design was the wrong frame; treat them as analogues that inform the discipline without dictating shape.|] Zero Minimum Zero [])) (ztest1 ([(Information Documentation)] Decision [meta import probe] Zero Minimum Zero [spirit])) (zupserttest ([(Information Documentation)] Decision [upsert probe v1] Zero Minimum Zero [spirit])) (zupst2 ([(Information Documentation)] Decision [upsert prod v2] Zero Minimum Zero [spirit])) (zyab ([(Technology (Software Data))] Decision [Spirit record observation should support filtering by certainty or magnitude, so review workflows can select low-confidence records such as removal candidates. *query processing*] Zero Minimum Zero []))]))
